  "summaries": [
    "The <b>Megaphone</b> is an <linked>accessory</linked> that can be obtained by killing <linked>Pixies</linked>, <linked>Green Jellyfish</linked>, <linked>Dark Mummies</linked>, or <linked>Blood Mummies</linked> with a <span class=\"chance\"><s>1*</s>1/100 (1%)</span> / <linked>2*1/50 (2%)</linked> chance. When equipped, it grants immunity to the <linked>Silenced</linked> <linked>debuff</linked>.",
    "It is one of the ingredients required to make the <linked>Countercurse Mantra</linked>, which is a <linked>crafting material</linked> required to make the <linked>Ankh Charm</linked>, an accessory further required to make the <linked>Ankh Shield</linked>.",
    "While the Megaphone is exclusive to <linked>Hardmode</linked> on the <linked>[img:Old-gen console version]</linked><linked> Old-gen console version</linked>, <linked>Nintendo 3DS</linked><linked>[img:Nintendo 3DS version]</linked><linked> version</linked>, and <linked>[img:Legacy tModLoader version]</linked><linked> Legacy tModLoader version</linked>, it can be obtained in <linked>pre-Hardmode</linked> on the <linked>[img:Desktop version]</linked><linked> Desktop version</linked>, <linked>[img:Console version]</linked><linked> Console version</linked>, and <linked>[img:Mobile version]</linked><linked> Mobile version</linked> by throwing a <linked>Nazar</linked> into <span class=\"eil\"><span><linked>Shimmer</linked></span><span class=\"eico s i1 i2 i4\" title=\"Desktop, Console and Mobile versions\"><b></b><i></i></span></span>."
